1
00:00:04,315 --> 00:00:09,670
This is one continuous lifecycle session of Radeon Voice Skill Foundry.

2
00:00:09,670 --> 00:00:16,972
The cinematic interface runs against an isolated Node API with a clean lifecycle data directory.

3
00:00:16,972 --> 00:00:23,787
This recording focuses on durability, compatibility, and recovery rather than repeating the GPU benchmark.

4
00:00:23,787 --> 00:00:35,471
Speech and compile results use the repository's deterministic fixtures, while the main Demo V2 shows the real Cloudflare-to-W7900 Qwen three A-S-R and four-B path.

5
00:00:35,471 --> 00:00:40,339
Every durable record shown next is created during this session.

6
00:00:42,841 --> 00:00:49,258
I open the Voice module and upload the twenty-point-three-nine second Chinese procedure.

7
00:00:49,258 --> 00:00:56,744
The deterministic A-S-R fixture returns the same transcript used by the real Radeon validation.

8
00:00:56,744 --> 00:01:07,974
Voice Evidence version zero point three measures level, clipping, silence, estimated signal-to-noise ratio, short dropout, multi-frame burst loss, and source integrity.

9
00:01:07,974 --> 00:01:17,065
The source passes at one hundred out of one hundred, and its transcript hash is stored server-side.

10
00:01:19,567 --> 00:01:26,573
The deterministic compiler now combines the spoken constraints, aligned action trace, and local policy retrieval.

11
00:01:26,573 --> 00:01:34,981
It generates the same typed policy surface used by the live product, including runtime-owned identifiers and safety guardrails.

12
00:01:34,981 --> 00:01:43,855
The trusted compile run is written to the isolated durable store and the interface advances into the Policy module.

13
00:01:46,569 --> 00:01:58,911
The generated policy denies automatic email sending, redacts salary data, opens review for missing ownership, and keeps calendar holds conditional on a due date.

14
00:01:58,911 --> 00:02:03,024
Seven positive and adversarial fixtures execute before promotion.

15
00:02:03,024 --> 00:02:04,567
All seven pass.

16
00:02:04,567 --> 00:02:17,937
`mail.send` remains denied, four governance receipts are issued, and the proof receives a compatibility manifest for the runtime, verifier, tools, policy, skill, and Voice Evidence schema.

17
00:02:20,572 --> 00:02:26,492
The verified result is saved into procedural memory with its original action contract.

18
00:02:26,492 --> 00:02:28,314
I immediately reuse it.

19
00:02:28,314 --> 00:02:38,788
The proven skill loads without regenerating the policy or fixtures, while the reuse counter and retrieval latency update inside the same browser session.

20
00:02:41,573 --> 00:02:50,512
Now the recording controller terminates the isolated Node API process and starts a fresh process with the same runtime identity.

21
00:02:50,512 --> 00:02:55,428
The browser UI remains open and reconnects to the recovered API.

22
00:02:55,428 --> 00:03:08,837
The saved skill, trusted compile run, verification result, Voice Evidence, and proof compatibility all survive the real process restart because they were atomically persisted rather than held only in memory.

23
00:03:11,576 --> 00:03:19,535
The controller performs a second real API restart, this time with a changed runtime model identity.

24
00:03:19,535 --> 00:03:23,017
The stored proof is not silently reused.

25
00:03:23,017 --> 00:03:33,464
After reload, the skill changes to revalidation required, explains that the runtime contract changed, and replaces the Reuse command with Revalidate.

26
00:03:35,965 --> 00:03:47,666
Revalidation creates a new child run bound to the changed runtime, reruns all seven fixtures, and restores compatibility.

27
00:03:47,666 --> 00:03:58,067
I confirm the skill is verified again, open the new Proof module, and download its package.

28
00:03:58,067 --> 00:04:11,068
The ZIP contains the skill, least-privilege policy, fixtures, receipts, retrieved evidence, source-bound Voice Evidence, compatibility manifest, and parent-child proof lineage.

29
00:04:11,068 --> 00:04:19,510
This completes voice to policy to proof, through restart, invalidation, and recovery, in one continuous session.
